{
  "paper_slug": "all-in-one",
  "plan_version": 1,
  "notes": "The SimFormer paper introduces a unified probabilistic diffusion model based on transformers that performs amortized Bayesian inference without requiring fixed priors, likelihoods, or simulator structures. It handles unstructured, missing, and time-dependent data via attention masks encoding domain knowledge, and supports on-the-fly conditioning. The implementation must modularize data generation, tokenization, transformer architecture, diffusion scoring, training, and inference entry points to reflect its novel joint learning of likelihood and posterior, dynamic conditioning, and dependency-aware attention.",
